# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase — client (browser) credentials
#
# This is a Vite app, so ONLY variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the
# browser bundle. The cloud sync / global leaderboard reads these two. If they
# are left empty the app runs 100% offline exactly as before (cloud is a no-op).
#
# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL             = the Project URL (https://xxxx.supabase.co)
#   VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY = the publishable / anon key (sb_publishable_… or legacy anon key)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=""
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=""
# Legacy alias — used as a fallback if PUBLISHABLE is not set.
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server-side secrets (auto-injected by the Vercel ↔ Supabase integration).
#
# These are NOT used by the browser app and MUST NEVER be VITE_-prefixed — that
# would leak them into the public client bundle. Kept here only so the Vercel
# integration's variable names round-trip. Use them for migrations / the
# Supabase CLI / server functions — never in src/.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SUPABASE_URL=""
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=""
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=""
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=""
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=""
SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=""

POSTGRES_DATABASE=""
POSTGRES_HOST=""
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=""
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL=""
POSTGRES_URL=""
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING=""
POSTGRES_USER=""
